\ls45\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Public IP Address:
\f1\b0  This is the 
\f4\b street address of the building
\f1\b0 . Anyone in the world can find this address and use it to get to the front door of the building. It's the only way to get in from the outside.\
\ls45\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Private IP Address:
\f1\b0  This is your 
\f4\b office number inside the building
\f1\b0  (e.g., Suite 2B). Once you are inside the building, you can use this private number to find your office, or a coworker can use it to send a message to you from their office down the hall. No one on the street knows what "Suite 2B" is\'97it only makes sense 
\f6\i inside
\f1\i0  the building.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

