\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 The Analogy: A Rented Office Space
\f1\b0 \

\fs29\fsmilli14667 Imagine you have rented an office space in a large office building. This office space represents your AWS instance.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls104\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Your AWS Instance:
\f1\b0  The rented office space. It has all your equipment (CPU, memory), your files (disk storage), and it's ready for you to work.\
\ls104\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
AWS:
\f1\b0  The building management company that owns and operates the office building.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Now, let's look at the two different actions you can take with your rented office space.\

\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 1. Stopping an Instance: Taking a Break
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls105\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Action:
\f1\b0  You decide you're going on vacation for a month. You don't need to use the office, but you want all your furniture, files, and equipment to be right where you left them when you return. So, you tell the building manager you want to put your lease on "hold" or "pause."\
\ls105\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
What happens:
\f1\b0  The building manager turns off the lights, the heating/AC, and locks the door to your specific office. They don't remove your furniture or files. They stop billing you for the electricity and other utility usage, but you're still "renting" the space. When you return from vacation, you just call them and say, "Please turn the power back on and unlock the door," and everything is exactly as you left it.\
\ls105\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Key points from the slide:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls105\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Stopping is preferred before termination":
\f1\b0  This is like pausing your lease instead of canceling it entirely. It's the right choice for a temporary break.\
\ls105\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"AWS bills based on instance running time":
\f1\b0  You stop paying for the utilities (running time) but you still hold onto the space and your stuff.\
\ls105\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Stopping instances avoids unnecessary charges":
\f1\b0  By putting the lease on hold, you save money on the utility bills for the month you're away.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf0 2. Terminating an Instance: Canceling the Lease
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls106\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Action:
\f1\b0  You decide you're never coming back to this office. You've found a new job and a new location, and you want to permanently end your relationship with the building. You tell the building manager you want to "terminate" your lease.\
\ls106\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
What happens:
\f1\b0  The building manager completely clears out your office. They remove all your furniture, shred your files, and prepare the space for a new tenant. It's gone forever. You can't just call them later and say, "Oops, can I have my old office back?" You would have to start from scratch and get a brand new one.\
\ls106\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Key points from the slide:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls106\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Terminate instances when no longer needed":
\f1\b0  This is the action you take when you are completely done with the resource.\
\ls106\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u9702 
\f4 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
