\fs28 \cf3 1. How do you automate EC2 creation using AWS CLI?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 To automate EC2 creation, you use the \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 aws ec2 run-instances\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  command.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls114\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Key Parameters:
\f0\b0  You must provide the \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 --image-id\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (AMI), \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 --count\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 --instance-type\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (e.g., t2.micro), \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 --key-name\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (for SSH), and \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 --security-group-ids\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 .\
\ls114\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Efficiency:
