\f2\b Shell Script
\f0\b0  or a 
\f2\b Python (Boto3)
\f0\b0  script to handle multiple requests without manual UI clicks.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 2. Explain the difference between Public and Private IPs.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls115\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Public IP:
\f0\b0  Think of this as the 
\f2\b street address
\f0\b0  of a building. It is reachable from the internet. You use this to SSH into your instance from your laptop.\
\ls115\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Private IP:
\f0\b0  Think of this as an 
\f2\b office number
\f0\b0  inside the building. It is only reachable within the AWS network (the VPC). It allows servers to talk to each other securely without going over the public internet.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 3. Why is \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 chmod 600\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  required for PEM files?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf3 AWS enforces a "strict" security policy for private keys. If the permissions are too open (e.g., others on your computer can read the file), the SSH client will reject the key to prevent potential theft.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls116\ilvl0\cf10 \cb11 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec10 6\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  = Owner can Read/Write.\
\ls116\ilvl0\cf10 \cb11 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec10 00\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  = Group and Others have zero access.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 4. Stopping vs. Terminating an Instance\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls117\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Stop:
\f0\b0  Like 
\f2\b pausing
\f0\b0  a lease. You stop paying for the "compute" (CPU/RAM), but the disk (EBS) and your files remain. You can start it back up later.\
\ls117\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Terminate:
\f0\b0  Like 
\f2\b canceling
\f0\b0  a lease. The instance is deleted, and unless you specifically configured otherwise, all data on that instance is destroyed. Billing stops entirely.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
