The Shebang (#!): Specifying the Script Interpreter: The first line of a shell script, called the shebang, is a special directive that tells the operating system which interpreter should be used to execute the script's commands.\
\ls120\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
