\f1\b0 Automation is a process to reduce manual activities. In the context of a Linux machine (whether on AWS, a local laptop, or a VM using software like Oracle VirtualBox), shell scripting is used for automation. As long as the same shell is used, a script can be executed on any Linux machine. The script itself can define which shell to use for execution.\
