\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The shebang must be the very first line of the script.\
\ls126\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The syntax is #! followed by the path to an interpreter (e.g., /bin/bash).\
\ls126\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
This line is called the 'shebang'.\
