\ls128\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
It explicitly tells the system to use the bash interpreter located at the /bin/bash path to execute the subsequent commands in the file.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf0 5. The Shebang (#!): First Line in a Shell Script
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls129\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
