\f1\b0 The permission formula is based on numbers: 4 for read, 2 for write, and 1 for execute. The total, 7 (4+2+1), grants all permissions. The command chmod 444 xyz sets permissions for the user (owner), the group, and everybody else, respectively. In this case, 444 means everyone gets read-only permissions.\
