The permissions of 'first_shell_script.sh' were changed to read-only (4).\
\ls137\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
When attempting to edit and save the file, the operation fails.\
\ls137\ilvl1\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
When trying to execute the file with './', a 'permission denied' error occurs because execute permission (1) is not granted.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls137\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Setting read, write, and execute permissions\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 chmod 777 first_shell_script.sh\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls137\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
