\f1\b0  The shebang (#!) is the first line of a shell script, and it specifies the interpreter that should be used to run the script. For shell scripting, this is typically #!/bin/bash or #!/bin/sh. This ensures that the script is executed with the correct shell, even if the user's default shell is different. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zsajhz2_50g&t=931"}}{\fldrslt \cf8 \ul \ulc8 15:31}}]\
