\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \strokec3 Part 1: Technical Interview Q&A\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf3 1. What is a "Shebang" in Linux scripting, and why is it mandatory?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf3 Answer:
\f0\b0  The shebang (\cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 #!\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ) is the first line of a script that tells the kernel which interpreter to use (e.g., \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 #!/bin/bash\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ). It is mandatory because, without it, the script might execute using the user's default shell (like \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 dash\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  or \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 zsh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ), which may have different syntax, leading to errors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 2. What is the difference between \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 /bin/sh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  and \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 /bin/bash\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf3 Answer:
\f0\b0  * 
\f2\b \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 /bin/sh
\f0\b0 \cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  is usually the Bourne shell or a POSIX-compliant shell like \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 dash\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 . It is faster but has fewer features.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf10 \cb11 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec10 /bin/bash
\f0\b0 \cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (Bourne Again Shell) is an improved version with more features (like arrays and double brackets \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 [[ ]]\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ).\
\ls162\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Critical Note:
\f0\b0  On modern systems like Ubuntu, \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 /bin/sh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  points to \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 dash\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 . If your script uses "bash-isms" but has a \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 #!/bin/sh\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  shebang, it will fail.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 3. Explain the numeric permission model (\cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 4\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 2\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 1\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 ).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf3 Answer:
\f0\b0  Permissions are represented by:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 4 (Read):
\f0\b0  Ability to view file content.\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 2 (Write):
\f0\b0  Ability to modify file content.\
\ls163\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 1 (Execute):
\f0\b0  Ability to run the file as a program.\uc0\u8232 They are summed for three groups: Owner, Group, and Others. For example, \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 chmod 755\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  means the owner has full access ($4+2+1=7$), while others can only read and execute ($4+1=5$).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

\f2\b\fs28 \cf3 \strokec3 4. Why use \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 touch\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  instead of \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 vim\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  in an automation script?\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa200\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf3 Answer:
\f0\b0  \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 touch\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  is non-interactive; it creates a file without opening an interface. \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 vim\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  is an interactive editor. If you try to create 1,000 files in a loop using \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 vim\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , the system will attempt to open 1,000 editor buffers, which will crash the session or consume all memory. \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 touch\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  is efficient for bulk creation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \strokec4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\partightenfactor0

