Shell Script Best Practices: set -e and set -o pipefail\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 Using 'set -e' in shell scripts ensures the script exits immediately upon encountering an error, preventing unnecessary execution of subsequent commands.\uc0\u8232 \'a0However, 'set -e' alone does not catch errors in piped commands,\u8232 \'a0so 'set -o pipefail' should also be used to ensure the script fails if any command in a pipeline fails.\
- 'set -e' exits the script when an error occurs.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \u8232 vim nodeHealth.sh\
\
\'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls186\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'a0\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Give the set + add-ons individually and Commands can be combined (e.g., 'set -e -x -o pipefail'), but it's suggested to keep them separate for flexibility\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\uc0\u8232 \'a0\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Without 'set -e', all lines in a script may execute even if an early command fails.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example order: create a user, create a file, add username to file; if user creation fails, subsequent steps are pointless.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
'set -e' does not catch errors in piped commands; only checks the last command in the pipe.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
'set -o pipefail' ensures the script fails if any command in a pipeline fails.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Best practice is to use both 'set -e' and 'set -o pipefail' together.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Commands can be combined (e.g., 'set -e -x -o pipefail'), but it's suggested to keep them separate for flexibility.\
\ls186\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Splitting commands into separate lines makes scripts easier to maintain and modify.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 \'a0\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
