DevOps Practice: Log File Error Detection\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \cf0 DevOps engineers routinely check log files for errors when applications fail. Log files can be very large and are often stored externally (e.g., GitHub, Google Storage, S3, Azure Blob). \uc0\u8232 Tools like 'cat', 'grep', 'curl', and 'wget' are used to retrieve and analyze logs.\
- Checking log files for errors is a daily task for DevOps engineers.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls188\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Log files may be stored on external platforms, not on the local machine.\
\ls188\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Use 'cat' and 'grep' to find errors in local log files.\
\ls188\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
