\f2\b\fs36 \cf3 \strokec3 4. Node Health & Monitoring (The "DevOps" Script)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls223\ilvl0
\fs24 \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 The Concept:
\f0\b0  Using \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 top\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 df -h\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 free -m\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 , and \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 nproc\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  to check if a server is "sick."\
\ls223\ilvl0
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Interview Q:
\f0\b0  
\f3\i "How do you find the Process ID (PID) of a hung application?"
\f0\i0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls223\ilvl1
\f2\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f10 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Answer:
\f0\b0  Use \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 ps -ef | grep <app_name>\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 . The second column is the PID.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls223\ilvl0
\f2\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 STAR Scenario:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sa200\partightenfactor0
\ls223\ilvl1
\f2\b \cf3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f10 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 S:
\f0\b0  Developers complained that the AWS EC2 instances were "slow" every Monday morning.\
\ls223\ilvl1
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f10 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 T:
\f0\b0  I needed to diagnose the root cause without manual login.\
\ls223\ilvl1
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f10 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 A:
\f0\b0  I wrote a health script that captured \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 top\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (CPU), \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 free\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (RAM), and \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 df\cf3 \cb1 \strokec3  (Disk) outputs and appended them to a log file in an S3 bucket.\
\ls223\ilvl1
\f2\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	
\f10 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 R:
\f0\b0  I discovered a Cron Job was running a heavy backup at the same time developers logged in. I rescheduled the job to 2:00 AM, resolving the performance complaints.\
