\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 The Question:
\f1\b0 \strokec2  
\f6\i \strokec2 "How do you handle a script that works on your machine but fails in a production environment?"
\f1\i0 \strokec2 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls225\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Situation:
\f1\b0  I developed a health monitoring script on my local Mac terminal that worked perfectly, but when deployed to a fleet of 
\f4\b Ubuntu servers
