\ls230\ilvl0
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Explanation\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 To retrieve data from a remote machine or URL in a shell script, you use the curl command. After fetching the entire log file with curl, you need to filter it to show only the lines containing errors. This is done by piping the output of curl to the grep command. grep searches for lines that match a specific pattern (like 'error') and prints only those matching lines.\
\ls230\ilvl0
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example of fetching a remote file and filtering its content\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 curl google.com | grep href\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls230\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
