\f1\b0 crontab functions like a task scheduler or an alarm for your commands. It is commonly used by system administrators to automate repetitive tasks. For example, instead of manually logging in every day at 6 p.m. to run a script that generates a system health report, an administrator can create a crontab entry. This entry will tell the system to automatically execute the script at 6 p.m. daily. The output of the script can be saved to a file or redirected to another location, like an S3 bucket.\
