\f2\b \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 set -x
\f0\b0 \cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 : Prints every command before it is executed, showing you exactly how variables are expanding. \uc0\u8232 \
\ls275\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\b \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 set -e
\f0\b0 \cf3 \cb1 \strokec3 : Ensures the script exits immediately if any command fails, preventing "cascading" errors. \uc0\u8232 \
\ls275\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 \uc0\u8232 
\f2\b \cf10 \cb11 \strokec10 $?
