\f2\b A
\f0\b0 : 
\f2\b High-Level Design (HLD)
\f0\b0  outlines the overall system architecture, including database choice and scalability. 
\f2\b Low-Level Design (LLD)
\f0\b0  specifies the technical details of functions, module interactions, and specific technical integrations. \uc0\u8232 \
