\f1\b0 Version Control Systems became popular because manual sharing of code (e.g., via Gmail or Slack) is impractical for large projects with hundreds or thousands of files. VCS allows developers to track changes, merge code, and revert to previous versions efficiently. For example, if a developer modifies 100 files on day one, 5 files on day two, and 50 files on day three, VCS can help identify and revert specific changes as needed.\
