\f1\b0 Organizations like Uber use branching strategies to manage code versions. For example, after three or six months, Uber creates a new release branch (e.g., release v3) from the latest master branch, performs testing, and ships the new version to customers. If a bug is reported three days after release, a hotfix branch is created to address the issue and merged into master and all relevant release branches. Feature branches are used for major changes, and the master branch remains the main, up-to-date branch.\
