Explanation\uc0\u8232 
\f1\b0 To integrate changes from one branch to another, use 'git merge', 'git rebase', or 'git cherry-pick'. Cherry-pick is suitable for single commits, but not practical for large numbers (e.g., 50,000 or 60,000 commits). Merge and rebase are better for bulk changes. Conflicts must be resolved by discussing with developers and editing the affected files.\
