10. Version Control System (VCS)
\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Explanation:
\f1\b0  A Version Control System (VCS) is a tool that helps manage changes to source code over time. It allows multiple developers to collaborate without overwriting each other's work. The mind map highlights two major problems that a VCS solves:\
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl2
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Sharing code among developers:
\f1\b0  It provides a central location for everyone to get the latest version of the code and share their changes.
\f4\b \
\ls290\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Maintaining multiple versions of code:
\f1\b0  It keeps a complete history of changes, allowing developers to track who changed what and when. This also allows them to revert to a previous, working version if a bug is introduced.
\f4\b \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl1\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Analogy:
\f1\b0  A VCS is a 
\f4\b collaborative time machine for a group project
\f1\b0 .\
\pard\tx1660\tx2160\pardeftab720\li2160\fi-2160\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl2\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Without a VCS, if two people work on the same document and save it, one person's work will be overwritten.\
\ls290\ilvl2\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f8 \uc0\u9702 
\f1 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
With a VCS (like Git), everyone has a full copy on their machine. When they are ready, they commit their changes (save a dated snapshot of their work) and push it to a central server. The VCS then automatically merges the changes and flags any conflicts. The "time machine" feature allows you to travel back to any previous version if needed.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example:
\f1\b0  A team of three developers is building a website. Developer A adds a new login page. Developer B fixes a bug on the homepage. They both work on their own code without affecting each other. They then use the VCS to share their code. If Developer A's new code introduces a bug, the team can use the VCS to revert the code back to the last working version before the new login page was added.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
