\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Explanation:
\f1\b0  AWS IAM is a service that allows you to manage access to your AWS resources. You can create users, assign roles, and define policies to control who can do what (e.g., a developer can access an EC2 instance but not delete an S3 bucket). This is the cornerstone of security in AWS.\
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Analogy:
\f1\b0  IAM is a 
\f4\b security guard for your AWS account
\f1\b0 . You give the security guard a list of rules (policies) that specify who can enter which room (resources) and what they are allowed to do.\
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example:
\f1\b0  To give a new developer access to your AWS account, you would create an IAM user for them. You would then attach a policy to that user that grants them permissions to launch and manage EC2 instances but prevents them from accessing your private data in S3.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl0
\f4\b\fs42\fsmilli21333 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
42. AWS EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud)
\f1\b0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Explanation:
\f1\b0  EC2 is a service that provides scalable virtual servers in the cloud. It allows you to launch instances with different configurations, operating systems, and memory options to suit various application needs. You have full control over the instance.\
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Analogy:
\f1\b0  A 
\f4\b rented office building with different-sized offices
\f1\b0 . You can choose a small office for a small team or an entire floor for a large one, and you can get more space or less space as your needs change.\
\ls290\ilvl1
\f4\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Example:
\f1\b0  You launch a t2.micro EC2 instance to run a small personal blog. As your blog grows in popularity, you can upgrade to a larger t2.medium instance to handle the increased traffic without having to migrate to a new server.\
